node.text:
.⁣
.⁣
Deadlifts are a compound movement which involve both the back and legs 🔥⁣
⁣
This can make it difficult to know which muscle group you should pair your deadlifts with 🤔⁣
⁣
I’ve found that either way works well but it really depends on how you structure the rest of your workouts throughout the week ✅⁣
⁣
Generally speaking .. training muscle groups more frequently can often lead to greater results .. but only if you can recover from the workload! 💡 ⁣
⁣
I’ve mainly paired my lower body training with deadlifts in the past .. but lately I’ve found that my recovery has been impaired from my other 2 lower body sessions throughout the week .. so I’ve had to adapt and re-organise my training split and decided to pair my back training with my deadlifts from this point forward 👌⁣
⁣
How do you structure your training ?⁣
Do you train deadlifts with legs or back ??⁣
.
Song🎵 Roman P - Our Way
#deadlifting #sumodeadlift #powerliftingwomen

node.title: Should Deadlifts Be Trained With Back or Legs?⁣

node.text:
.⁣
.⁣
Sumo deadlifts are a great movement but many people struggle to get into a good position due to a lack of hip mobility 💡⁣
⁣
So here’s a mobility routine you can use on a daily basis (if you’re excessively tight) or you can simply use it as a warm up for your deadlift session 🙏⁣
⁣
It should only take around 10 mins once you get familiar with the routine 💥 ⁣
⁣
✅ FOAM ROLLING (30sec each on each side)⁣
i) Quads ⁣
ii) Glutes ⁣
iii) Adductors ⁣
iv) Hip Flexors⁣
📝 Move slowly over the muscle but pause and hold on a pressure point (if it’s extra tight) until it loosens ⁣
⁣
✅ ACTIVE STRETCHES (30sec each on each side)⁣
v) Pigeon Pose ⁣
vi) Lizard Pose⁣
📝 Move back and forward aiming to get more range each time⁣
⁣
✅ DYNAMIC STRETCHES (10 reps each)⁣
vii) Hip Fire Hydrants ⁣
viii) Rolling V Sits ⁣
⁣
✅ MOBILITY DRILLS (10 reps each)⁣
ix) Paused Bulgarian Split Squats ⁣
x) Wide Foot Mountain Climbers⁣
⁣
You’ll also see my top set for the day which was 150kg / 330lb for 5 reps 🏋️‍♀️⁣
⁣
SAVE this post and try it for yourself 💕

#sumodeadlift #hipmobility #deadlifting

node.title: Warming up for a SUMO DEADLIFT 🔥⁣

node.text:
.
.⁣
Do you have issues with your hips when you squat ?? 🤔⁣
⁣
Here’s a warm up routine you can use to loosen up the hips and prepare you for your workout 🔥⁣
⁣
➡️ FOAM ROLL⁣
i) Hip Flexors x 30-60sec each⁣
ii) Adductors x 30-60sec each⁣
➡️ STRETCHES ⁣
iii) Hip Fire Hydrants x 10-20 each ⁣
iv) Frog Stretch x 10-20 ⁣
➡️ MOBILITY EXERCISES⁣
v) World’s Greatest Stretch x 10 each⁣
vi) Hip Aeroplanes x 10 each⁣
vii) Bulgarian Split Squats x 10 each ⁣
⁣
Here’s a workout you can also try which was focused on BUILDing the Squat and the Hamstrings 💪⁣
⁣
1. Low Bar Squats 3x5⁣
2. Pin Squats 3x6⁣
3. DB Romanian Deadlifts 5x10⁣
4. Glute Ham Raises 5x12 ⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 Discovery by Roman P⁣
#legsworkout #athomegym #workoutfromhome

node.title: Warming up the Hips before SQUATS 💡⁣

node.text:
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
There was a time in my training journey where I never used to take my warm ups seriously 🙅‍♀️ ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
I think it’s hard to appreciate their importance .. but that tends to change pretty quick after you get hurt from not warming up properly! 🤕⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
This is what happened to me and ever since then - I’ve made sure my warm ups are a priority before every session 💯⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
It should be noted that an effective warm up should go well beyond simply “warming up” the body 💡⁣⁣⁣
⁣
One of their other objectives is to improve your joint mobility and muscular stability ✅⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
This will help you move better, feel better, perform better, as well as drastically decrease your likelihood of injury 🙏⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Here’s a thorough warm up for the UPPER BODY as an example (this should only take 6-8 mins) 💥⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
WARM UP ROUTINE⁣⁣⁣
i) Downward Dog x 10 (3 sec holds)⁣⁣⁣
ii) Side Lying Thoracic Spine Rotations x 10ea⁣⁣⁣
iii) Band Dislocations x 20⁣⁣⁣
iv) Band Pull Aparts x 20⁣⁣⁣
v) Band Face Pulls x 20⁣⁣⁣
vi) Band Straight Arm Pulldowns x 20⁣⁣⁣
vii) KB Bottoms Up Single Arm Press x10ea⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
I’ve also included a workout for you to try which was focused on the SHOULDERS + BACK (taken straight from my program BUILD 2.0) 🙌⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
1. Standing Barbell Press 4x6⁣⁣⁣
2. Chin Ups (Can Be Assisted) 4x4⁣⁣⁣
3a. Barbell Curl + Press 4x8⁣⁣⁣
3b. Dumbbell Sir Charles Lateral Raise 4x8⁣⁣⁣
4. Dumbbell Single Arm Row 4x10⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
.⁣
Do your workouts follow a set structure or do you make them up at random ?? 🤔⁣⁣
⁣⁣
My sessions always follow a set structure which is made up of the following 3 categories:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1️⃣ STRENGTH: Primary Movement⁣⁣
✅ Perform a heavy barbell movement to develop functional strength and power ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2️⃣ ASSISTANCE: Secondary Movement⁣⁣
✅ Perform a variation of the primary movement to emphasise and strengthen a specific muscle group or movement pattern⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3️⃣ HYPERTROPHY: Accessory Movements⁣⁣
✅ Perform a wide range of exercises utilising various pieces of equipment (such as dumbbells and machines) to increase muscle mass ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve found this structure works really well to increase your strength and muscle - using a combination of both powerlifting and bodybuilding 💪⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I call it “Power-Building” 💡⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is the same structure found in all of my BUILD Programs 💥⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s an example of my Lower Body workout today:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Low Bar Squat 3x5⁣⁣
2. Pin Squats 3x5⁣⁣
3a. Power Squat Machine 3x10⁣⁣
3b. Seated Leg Curls 3x10⁣⁣
4a. Walking Lunges 3x20⁣⁣
4b. Leg Extensions 3x20 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

.⁣
.⁣
Unilateral movements refers to movements that only involve a single limb (arm or leg) at one time ✅ ⁣
⁣
The first 3 movements in this video are all examples of unilateral movements: ⁣
⁣
1. Bulgarian Split Squats⁣
2. Single Leg RDL’s⁣
3. Lying Extended Range Hip Abductions⁣
⁣
If you were to only perform bilateral movements (involving both arms or legs) in your training .. you run the risk of developing imbalances in your body ⚠️⁣
⁣
Generally speaking - most people will have a dominate side that will produce more force which means the weaker side can can often get neglected 🙅‍♀️⁣
⁣
If this is left untreated - it can create all sorts of postural issues and increase the likelihood of injury 🤕⁣
⁣
So it’s definitely a good idea to include some unilateral work in your training to reduce the risk of this occurring 🙏⁣
⁣
I always perform a few of these movements at the beginning of each workout to ensure my body is moving correctly before loading it up with maximal weights 💡⁣
⁣
These were the other movements in my squat session: ⁣
⁣
1. Low Bar Squats⁣
2. Box Squats⁣
3. Leg Press⁣
4a. Zercher Walking Lunges⁣
4b. Leg Extensions ⁣
#BUILDProgram⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 Elevations by Jack Shore 
#lowerbodyworkout #fitnessvideo 
#fitnessadvice

Sometime we can be our own worst enemy .. we tend to complicate simple tasks and make them feel so overwhelming that we never take action 🙅‍♀️⁣
⁣
Has anyone done this with their training ??⁣
⁣
One thing to remember .. you’re only lifting things up and putting them back down 🤷‍♀️⁣
⁣
Get yourself a good program and just show up 💯⁣
⁣
Sometimes the battle is just showing up .. but I promise you .. if you overcome that barrier - you be grateful that you did 💕⁣
⁣
These were the exercises in my lower body workout: ⁣
⁣
1. Squats⁣
2. Power Squat Machine⁣
3a. Walking Lunges⁣
3b. Leg Extensions⁣
4. Calf Raises ⁣
⁣
Also make sure you check out my program BUILD available now on the @sweat app 📲 ⁣

.⁣
.⁣
Are you a fan of the foam roller ?? 🤔 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It really should be called the PAIN roller 😂⁣⁣
⁣⁣
But in all seriousness .. the foam roller is a great way relieve muscle tension / soreness and can also help improve the range of motion of your joints 💡⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I find that it’s a great tool to use at the very beginning of your workout to loosen up - or - right before bed to improve recovery and help you relax 💯⁣⁣
⁣⁣
📝 NOTE: If used at the beginning of a workout - you should follow up the rolling with a regular warm up because whilst the foam roller loosens the muscles .. it also relaxes them! 😴 So it’s important to include some other movements to stimulate blood flow and “wake them up again” before beginning your lifting ✅⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s some of the areas that I like to roll to prepare myself for a SQUAT session: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
➡️ Hip Flexors⁣⁣
➡️ ITB’s⁣⁣
➡️ Glutes (use lacrosse ball for more pressure)⁣⁣
➡️ Adductors (use barbell for more pressure)⁣⁣
⁣⁣
These were the other movements in the workout: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Low Bar Squats⁣⁣
2. Box Squats ⁣⁣
3. Zercher Reverse Lunges⁣⁣
4. Leg Extensions ⁣⁣
5. Calf Raises (not shown)⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Here’s 3 active stretches that you can use to help you improve your depth on a squat 🙏⁣
⁣
1️⃣ Couch Stretch (Loosen Hip Flexors) ⁣
2️⃣ Frog Stretch (Loosen Adductors)⁣
3️⃣ Elevated Bent Knee Stretch (Loosen Calves)⁣
⁣
Aim to hold the lengthened position for a 1-2 count then release the tension and repeat for 10-20 reps (aim to get further each rep) ✅⁣
⁣
I’ve also included the rest of my session which involved some high rep squats and other exercises to BUILD the quads 💪⁣
⁣
Right now I’m undulating my training by alternating between high rep weeks and low rep weeks 🙋‍♀️ This is a structure used in my program for the #SWEATChallenge 🏆⁣
⁣
These were my efforts last fortnight compared to my squats today: ⁣
⁣
Last Fortnight ➡️ 15,12,10 @ 70,77.5,85kg⁣
Today’s Efforts ➡️ 12,10,8 @ 80,87.5,95kg ⁣
⁣
Note that small changes (2.5kg increases) might not seem like much but it definitely adds up over time !! 💯 So for anyone currently doing my program - always do your best to add a little bit of weight each session wherever possible 💕⁣

node.text:
are one of the most beneficial exercises you can perform in the gym 💯 .. but they are also one of the most intimidating 😳⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you’re someone that wants to start squatting and lift heavier .. this would be an appropriate progression to build your technique and confidence: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
PHASE 1 - FRONT SQUATS⁣⁣
➡️ These force you to stay in a more upright position and increase the range of motion - this will help prepare you by building your mobility in the hips and ankles⁣⁣
⁣⁣
PHASE 2 - BOX SQUATS ⁣⁣
➡️ These teach you how to initiate the movement with your hips - this will teach you how to sit back and provide you with a physical point of contact to guide your depth and catch you if you fall⁣⁣
⁣⁣
PHASE 3 - REGULAR SQUATS ⁣⁣
➡️ After the first 2 phases you should feel confident and ready to attempt regular back squats and start building up in weight! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is the exact progression I use in my BUILD Beginner Program to prepare newer lifters for squats 🙏⁣⁣
⁣⁣
All of these movements have unique benefits and I still use them all to this day 💯 In this video you’ll see I started with regular squats and then transitioned into front squats 🙌⁣⁣
⁣⁣
These were all of the exercises in my workout which now completes Day 1 (Week 2) of the #SWEATChallenge ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Squats (Top Set was 105kg / 231lb x 5)⁣⁣
2. Front Squats (Top Set was 70kg / 154lb x 5)⁣⁣
3a. Dumbbell Reverse Lunges⁣⁣
3b. Paused Leg Exensions⁣⁣
3c. Regular Leg Extensions⁣⁣
4. Calf Raises ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

.⁣
You might think I look happy to start these squats .. but the truth is that I was just a bit delirious thanks to the sets leading up to it 🙃😂⁣⁣
⁣⁣
In this session I used a pyramid loading strategy for my squats 💥⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This means that the reps decreased each set but the weight increased 💡 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
These were my sets for the session:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SET 1 ➡️ 15 reps at 70kg / 154lb⁣⁣
SET 2 ➡️ 12 reps at 77.5kg / 170lb⁣⁣
SET 3 ➡️ 10 reps at 85kg / 187lb (video)⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Using this sort of rep scheme is a great way to increase the intensity and variety in your session and works really well to BUILD more muscle 💪⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As much as I was cursing all the reps in this session... I know it’s going to have a great impact on my training and body 💯 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
These were the other accessory movements in the session that followed after the squats:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2. Leg Press ⁣⁣
3a. DB Walking Lunges ⁣⁣
3b. 2 Up + 1 Down Leg Extensions ⁣⁣
3c. Regular Leg Extensions ⁣⁣
4. Calf Presses⁣⁣
⁣⁣
DAY 1 of the #SWEATChallenge complete ✅⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SONG 🎵 Invincible by Jonezen ⁣⁣

Here’s a strength focused session for the LOWER BODY 🏋️‍♀️⁣
⁣
I also wanted to quickly address a common question I’ve been getting lately which is...⁣
⁣
What’s the difference between my program BUILD vs my new program Strength & Resistance ??⁣
⁣
✅ BUILD (Strength & Hypertrophy Program)⁣
⁣
➡️ Primary Objective is to Increase 1RM Strength⁣
➡️ Secondary Objective is to Increase Muscle Mass⁣
➡️ Reps Mainly Range Between 1-10 Reps⁣
➡️ Exercises Remain More Consistent Throughout the Program to Improve Technique ⁣
⁣
✅ S&R (Hypertrophy & Conditioning Program)⁣
⁣
➡️ Primary Objective is to Increase Muscle Mass⁣
➡️ Secondary Objective is to Improve Conditioning / Endurance (Fat Loss)⁣
➡️ Reps Mainly Range Between 8-20 Reps⁣
➡️ Exercises Vary on a Regular Basis to Prevent Excessive Fatigue⁣
⁣
Make sure check out the programs on the @sweat app if you’re interested in trying them out 🔥⁣
⁣
As for this specific session .. this is much more of a BUILD Style Workout which is all about Simple, Heavy, Basic Strength Work 💪 ⁣
⁣
1. Hatfield Squats 3x10⁣
2. Sumo Deadlifts 3x5⁣
3. Hip Thrusts 20,15,12,10⁣
4. Romanian Deadlifts 10,8,6,5⁣

node.text:
I can’t express the importance of having a GOAL with your training 🏆⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you don’t .. you’ll likely find yourself aimlessly going through workouts struggling to find any motivation 🤷‍♀️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Lifting weights is HARD...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So it’s absolutely crucial for you to have a REASON to justify pushing yourself through that hardship 💯⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So when it comes to goal setting - make sure you use these 3 rules 👇⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1️⃣ SPECIFIC: What are you trying to accomplish?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2️⃣ MEASURABLE: How much are you trying to accomplish?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3️⃣ TIMEFRAME: When are you planning on accomplishing it? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
What’s one of your goals !? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s the workout from the video which was focused specifically on increasing my strength on the Bench Press and building my overall Upper Body Strength (which is one of my major goals right now!) 💪 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Bench Press 8,6,5,3⁣⁣
2. T Bar Rows 4x8⁣⁣
3a. Duffalo Bar (or DB) Bench Press 3x10⁣⁣
3b. Incline DB Chest Supported Row 3x10⁣⁣
4a. 1+1/4 Rep DB Skull Crush 3x12 ⁣⁣
4b. Fat Bar (or DB) Bicep Curls 3x12⁣⁣
5. Rope Face Pulls 3x15⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SONG 🎵 Easy by K Sparks ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#gymworkouts #strengthcoach #workoutplan

node.text:
You are not what has happened to you .. you are what YOU decide to become 💯⁣
⁣
It can be very easy to fall into the trap of blame or shame .. trust me I’ve been there 😔⁣
⁣
We often blame others, or shame ourselves, for our inability to move forward and make progress...⁣
⁣
But what I’ve found, is that change is only ever possible when you decide to let go of things like regret and guilt .. and instead make an effort to take RESPONSIBILITY for your actions💡 ⁣
⁣
Because the truth is...⁣
⁣
You are where you are now because of the decisions that YOU have made up until this point🔥⁣
⁣
So if you want to break out of the rut you’re in...⁣
⁣
Accept that the outcome is entirely dependent on YOU 🙏⁣
⁣
The power is in your hands 💥 ⁣
⁣
Progression is possible whenever YOU’RE ready to move on and take ACTION !!⁣
⁣
So decide what you want, and get after it ❤️⁣
⁣
#gymquotes #gyminspiration #workoutinspiration

Here’s a workout to strengthen your UPPER BODY 💪 ⁣
⁣
Let me also take a moment to thank everyone that signed up to my NEW Strength & Resistance Program ❤️⁣
⁣
The response has been so overwhelming and I’m so excited for you guys to try out some of the new workouts !! 🤩⁣
⁣
Here’s a similar style of session that you’ll find within the program...⁣
⁣
➡️ STRENGTH PYRAMID ⁣
1. Seated DB Arnold Press 10,8,5,10-20⁣
⁣
➡️ HYPERTROPHY WORK ⁣
2. Cable 1 Arm Row 4x10ea⁣
⁣
➡️ HYPERTROPHY PYRAMID⁣
3. DB Bench Press 20,15,12,10⁣
⁣
➡️ SUPERSET⁣
4a. Cable 1 Arm Reverse Fly 3x15ea⁣
4b. Cable 1 Arm Tricep Pushdown 3x15ea⁣
⁣
➡️ TRI-SET⁣
5a. EZ Bar Overhead Tricep 3x10⁣
5b. EZ Bar Upright Rows 3x10⁣
5c. EZ Bar Close Grip Push Ups 3xMAX⁣
⁣
As you can see there’s LOTS of different techniques within each workout which will give you plenty of variety and force you to push beyond your comfort zone !! 🔥 ⁣
⁣
Don’t forget there’s also a Foundations Program for those newer to lifting as well as the main Strength & Resistance Program which is suitable for anyone wanting to challenge themselves in the gym 🏆⁣
⁣
Click the link in my bio for a FREE 7 Day Trial of the @Sweat App and give the program a try this week !! 🙊⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 A.N.C by Sycosis ⁣
⁣
#workoutplan #gymworkouts #upperbody

I have some exciting news !! 🙊🤩⁣
⁣
My NEW Strength and Resistance Program was released today in the @sweat app 📲😍⁣
⁣
(Click the link in my bio for a FREE 7 Day Trial and check it out!)⁣
⁣
This program is suitable for any women that want to...⁣
⁣
✅ Increase Lean Muscle Mass ⁣
✅ Decrease Body Fat ⁣
⁣
The program is different from my other programs because it uses...⁣
⁣
➡️ Stimulation Work (Improve Muscle Activation)⁣
➡️ Higher Rep Work (Mostly in the 6-20 Range)⁣
➡️ Pyramids (Making Volume Work More Enjoyable)⁣
➡️ Lots of Variety (Different Exercises Every Week)⁣
➡️ High Intensity Techniques (Such as Tri-Sets) ⁣
⁣
Here’s an example of one of the workouts which was focused on the QUADS + HAMSTRINGS 🦵 ⁣
⁣
🔥 STIMULATION⁣
1a. Single Leg Leg Extension 3x10⁣
1b. DB Split Squat 3x10-15ea ⁣
⁣
🏋️‍♀️ STRENGTH PYRAMID⁣
2. Heel Elevated Squats 10,8,5,10-20⁣
⁣
💪 HYPERTROPHY PYRAMID⁣
3. DB Romanian Deadlift 20,15,12,10⁣
⁣
🔄 SUPERSET⁣
4a. Single Leg Leg Press 4x20ea⁣
4b. Single Leg RDL 4x10ea⁣
⁣
🥵 TRI-SET⁣
5a. Leg Extensions 3x20⁣
5b. Prone Leg Curls 3x20⁣
5c. Goblet Squat 3x40sec⁣
⁣
I can’t wait for you all to try it out !! 😁⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 Lies by NM⁣
⁣
#legsworkout #trainingprogram #fitnessprogress

node.text:
People often ask me “why I deadlift in Socks instead of Shoes” 🤔 ⁣
⁣
So here we go…⁣
⁣
➡️ RANGE OF MOTION⁣
🧦 Socks place you closer to the ground (shortening the range of motion)⁣
👟 Shoes elevate you higher off the floor (the sole within your shoes forces you to lift from a deficit)⁣
⁣
➡️ STABILITY⁣
🧦 Socks make it easier to ground yourself which helps you disperse weight more evenly against the floor (improving your stability)⁣
👟 Shoes often have a sponge-like sole which makes them very unstable and also very challenging to disperse weight evenly throughout your entire foot ⁣
⁣
One more added benefit of HIGH SOCKS is that they PROTECT your shins from being scraped by the bar which is especially important for Sumo Deadlifts (because we want that bar as close to your shins as possible in order to maintain good technique) 💡 ⁣
⁣
#sumodeadlift #deadlifting #powerliftingwomen

node.text:
Do you have a fixed mindset or a growth mindset ?? 🤔 ⁣
⁣
Here’s the difference...⁣
⁣
FIXED MINDSET ⁣
➡️ If I fail .. I feel hopeless and give up ⁣
➡️ If I don’t know something .. I won’t try ⁣
➡️ If you succeed .. I feel jealous ⁣
➡️ If you give me advice .. I’ll listen but won’t take action ⁣
⁣
GROWTH MINDSET⁣
➡️ If I fail .. I learned a lesson and will try again⁣
➡️ If I don’t know something .. I’ll figure it out ⁣
➡️ If you succeed .. I feel inspired⁣
➡️ If you give me advice .. I’ll listen and take immediate action⁣
⁣
A fixed mindset will keep you in a FIXED position 💯⁣
⁣
If you’re struggling to make progress right now...⁣
⁣
Stop waiting for the right moment...⁣
And stop searching for the perfect plan...⁣
⁣
Seek help from those around you and open yourself up to GROWTH 🙌⁣
⁣
#gyminspiration #gymquotes #fitnessinspo

Here’s a workout to target your BACK + TRICEPS 🔥💪⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Make sure you SAVE this one and try it for yourself 💯🙏⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. DB 1 Arm Rows 4x8ea⁣⁣
2. Lat Pulldown 4x10⁣⁣
3. Supinated Single Arm High Row 3x12ea⁣⁣
4. Cable Straight Arm Pulldown 3x15⁣⁣
5. Seated Dips 4x8-10⁣⁣
6a. Tricep Pushdowns 3x12-15⁣⁣
6b. Close Grip Bench Push Ups 3xMAX⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SONG 🎵 Long Time by S.O.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#gymworkouts #backworkouts #tricepsworkout

node.text:
SHOULDERS + BICEPS are probably my most favourite muscle group to train 💪🔥🙊😏⁣
⁣
If you’re anything like me and enjoy a good Shoulder and Bicep workout .. then make sure you SAVE this one and give it a try 💯⁣
⁣
Here’s the full workout ⬇️⁣
⁣
1a. Cable Single Arm Front Raise 3x15ea⁣
1b. Cable Reverse Fly 3x15ea⁣
2. DB Curl into Arnold Press 15,12,10⁣
3a. Incline Barbell Front Raise 3x10⁣
3b. Incline Barbell Curl 3x10⁣
4a. EZ Bar Single Arm Lateral Raise 3x12ea⁣
4b. EZ Bar Single Arm Press 3xMAX⁣
5a. Kneeling Cable Curls 3x15⁣
5b. Standing Cable Curls 3xMAX⁣
⁣
Also .. time is running out if you’re still hoping to sign up for the @sweat challenge !! 😱⁣
⁣
Make sure you register before SUNDAY if you still want to join us 🔥⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 The Dark by WEARETHEGOOD⁣
⁣
#gymworkouts #bicepworkout #shouldersworkout

node.text:
Here’s a session to target your LOWER BODY if you’re running short on time ⏱👌⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The workout consists of 2 Tri-Sets (which is something we discussed in a recent post) ✅ ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For those that missed it...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
A Tri-Set requires you to perform 3 different exercises with minimal rest in between 💡 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m a big fan of these because they allow you to get more done in a shorter time frame and also work really well to increase your heart rate which helps expend more energy during your session 🔥⁣⁣
⁣⁣
…maybe one day I’ll write a full program to properly demonstrate how you can incorporate these into your training 🤷‍♀️😜⁣⁣
⁣⁣
But for now... here’s a workout to try as an example 😘⁣⁣
⁣⁣
➡️ TRI-SET 1: Quads 🦵 ⁣⁣
i) Zercher Lunge 4x10ea ⁣⁣
ii) 2 Up + 1 Down Leg Extensions 4x10ea ⁣⁣
iii) Sissy Squats (Machine or Free Standing) 4xMAX⁣⁣
⁣⁣
➡️ TRI-SET 2: Glutes and Hamstrings 🍑 ⁣⁣
i) Barbell Hip Thrust 4x10⁣⁣
ii) Banded DB Romanian Deadlift 4x10⁣⁣
iii) Glute Ham Raise (or Nordic Leg Curls) 4xMAX⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SONG 🎵 Make My Move by Oliver Michael ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#lowerbodyworkout #workoutideas #resistancetraining

node.text:
Here’s a workout to target your SHOULDERS + TRICEPS 💥💪⁣
⁣
Make sure you SAVE this post and try it some time this week 💯⁣
⁣
1. Seated DB Shoulder Press 4x6-8⁣
2. Bench Press 4x6-8⁣
3a. Smith Machine JM Press 4x8-10⁣
3b. Smith Machine Behind the Neck Press 4x8-10⁣
4a. Single Arm Cable Tricep Pushdown 4x10ea⁣
4b. Single Arm Cable Reverse Fly 4x20ea⁣
5a. DB Lateral Raise 4x10⁣
5b. DB Arnold Press 4x20⁣
⁣
As a side note for all my ladies doing the #sweatchallenge 💁‍♀️⁣
⁣
Get ready to pump up both the volume and intensity as we transition into Week 3 🔥😏⁣
⁣
For anyone not currently doing the challenge...⁣
⁣
You’re still welcome to join us for the final 4 Weeks !! 🙊⁣
⁣
Simply download the @sweat app by clicking the link in my bio and try it out for a free 7 day trial 🤩⁣
⁣
SONG 🎵 GO! by Akinyemi⁣
⁣
#tricepsworkout #powerliftingwomen #strengthcoach

node.text:
When we are younger .. we try to meet the expectations of our parents...⁣
⁣
But eventually - most of us end up deterring from their opinions in the hopes to find our own way of doing things...⁣
⁣
However when we do this .. we’re then typically subjected to what our family, friends and work colleagues expect from us...⁣
⁣
Or if it’s not people it could just be the expectations within our society...⁣
⁣
Either way .. we’re constantly bombarded with external forces telling who we should be and what we should represent.⁣
⁣
I’ve found this can make it virtually impossible to ever truly know yourself.⁣
⁣
I know for myself...⁣
⁣
I’ve really struggled to just be ME. ⁣
⁣
I feel a huge pressure to live up to the expectations of social media and the fitness industry. ⁣
⁣
Even though I’m technically “in it”...⁣
I often don’t feel “enough” to be in it...⁣
⁣
I’ve had many people send me messages telling me what they expect from me...⁣
⁣
They’ve told me think I should be leaner... ⁣
They think I should be stronger...⁣
They think I should be smarter...⁣
Ect..⁣
⁣
And I’ll be honest...⁣
I’d be lying if I said I’d never let it get to me.⁣
⁣
I haven’t yet worked out the cure to deal with all of these expectations...⁣
⁣
But here’s an antidote that’s been helpful to stay true to yourself and better manage the harsh opinions of others and...⁣
⁣
1. Know what you stand for⁣
2. Know where you want to go⁣
⁣
If you know your VALUES then it becomes hard for others to persuade you .. and if you know your INTENTION then it can be hard for people to ever steer you off track. ⁣
⁣
So I’d encourage you to get clear on those things and hold true to them - no matter what anyone says! ⁣
⁣
That’s something that’s helped me and I hope it helps you too ❤️ ⁣
⁣
#gyminspiration #workoutinspiration #fitnesswoman
